Create a Single Instance in AWS 

Install Terraform in the running instance

How to install Terraform on a EC2 instance and use IAM service to securely perform Terraform commands

First things first. Update the Linux instance.

sudo yum update -y

Once you are done, you will se update completed output.

Install Amazon utils

sudo yum install -y yum-utils

Add hashicorp repo

sudo yum-config-manager --add-repo https://rpm.releases.hashicorp.com/AmazonLinux/hashicorp.repo

Now the environment is set, you can install terraform

sudo yum -y install terraform

Finally check to see that it is installed properly.

terraform â€” version






